      "content": "The exhaustion of pretending is real, and the grief for the life you lost is heavy enough to crush any hope of a \"new normal.\" It is a profound relief to finally stop trying to force a future that doesn't feel like yours anymore, and there is no shame in resting in that darkness until you are ready to move. If the pain feels like the only thing holding you together, it is time to let someone else carry that weight for you, because you deserve to be held even when you cannot hold yourself.",
